div.p:
5069. For Riefler and Lovitt from Department and FEA. Reference your 5060, June 26th. We hope that a statement similar to that in our 5005, June 24th can be included in clinching agreement on ceilings and request that you make every effort to have it included. We believe the Swiss may well feel that opportunity for revisions in light of changed conditions would be in their interest as well as ours. However, we will not insist on its inclusion if (1) in Bern’s opinion such a clause would jeopardize prompt conclusion of agreement, or if Swiss would insist on a parallel escape clause which might release them from ceilings for reasons other than action taken by us or with our consent as specified in Keller’s letter of December 19th;
Foreign Relations, 1943, vol. ii, p. 892. and (2) MEW and EWD are agreed and satisfied that the
Foot–Riefler letter of December 19th, mentioned in your reference telegram, covers the kind of eventuality suggested by you.
